      eid = {64},
    pages = {64},
 abstract = "{We present the results of structure analyses for a large sample of 426
Ly{$\alpha$} emitters (LAEs) at z \~{} 2.2 that are observed with the Hubble
Space Telescope/Advanced Camera for Surveys and WFC3-IR during deep
extra-galactic legacy surveys. We confirm that the merger fraction and
the average ellipticity of LAE's stellar component are 10\%-30\% and
0.4-0.6, respectively, that are comparable with previous study results.
We successfully identify that some LAEs have a spatial offset between
Ly{$\alpha$} and stellar-continuum emission peaks,
{$\delta$}$_{Lyalpha}$, by \~{}2.5-4 kpc beyond our statistical
errors. To uncover the physical origin of strong Ly{$\alpha$} emission
found in LAEs, we investigate the Ly{$\alpha$} equivalent width (EW)
dependences of three structural parameters: merger fraction,
{$\delta$}$_{Lyalpha}$, and ellipticity of stellar distribution in
the range of EW(Ly{$\alpha$}) = 20-250 {\AA}. Contrary to expectations,
we find that the merger fraction does not significantly increase with
Ly{$\alpha$} EW. We reveal an anti-correlation between
